Brazil to Get $1 Billion Credit From U.S. Ex-Im Bank, Valor Says

-- B y   I u r i   D a n t a s
-- 
2011-03-21T13:01:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/brazil-to-get-1-billion-credit-from-u-s-ex-im-bank-valor-says.html
The U.S. Export-Import Bank will
lend  Brazil  $1 billion to help the South American country
prepare for the 2014  World Cup  and 2016 Olympic games, Valor
Economico newspaper reported, citing an interview with bank
Chairman Fred Hochberg.  The bank is ready to release the first $300 million of a
previously approved $2 billion credit line to help Brazilian
manufacturers import U.S. machinery and equipment, the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Iuri Dantas in Brasilia at 
 idantas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  